Checks for jarl-ignore-chunk comments that use a single-line form instead of the required Quarto YAML array form.



In Quarto and R Markdown documents, #| comments are parsed as YAML chunk options. The single-line form
#| jarl-ignore-chunk any_is_na: &lt;reason&gt;
is not idiomatic YAML and therefore Quarto will not compile. The correct form is a YAML array:
#| jarl-ignore-chunk:
#|   - any_is_na: &lt;reason&gt;



#| jarl-ignore-chunk any_is_na: &lt;reason&gt;
any(is.na(x))
Use instead:
#| jarl-ignore-chunk:
#|   - any_is_na: &lt;reason&gt;
any(is.na(x))

