Checks for duplicated function definitions in R packages.



Having two functions with the same name is likely an error since development tools such as devtools::load_all() will only load one of them. This rule looks for function definitions shared across files in the same R package, meaning files that are in a folder named “R” whose parent folder has a DESCRIPTION file.
This rule doesn’t have an automatic fix.



# In "R/foo1.R":
foo &lt;- function(x) {
  x + 1
}

# In "R/foo2.R":
foo &lt;- function(x) {
  x + 2
}

# Function "foo" is defined in two different scripts in the same package,
# which is likely due to a mistake.

